coding.display: Finding related to ability to latch on to breast for feeding

text.div: Patient:
Practitioner: 123

dosageInstruction.text: If possible by oxygen mask with reservoir at 10-15L/min
Start  3  dispersible tablet(s) Amoxicillin (250mg)   or 15 ml (250mg / 5ml syrup)    twice per day for 5 days

medicationCodeableConcept.text: Oral Rehydration Solution (ORS) by Nasal Gastric Tube (clinic or hospital)

dosageInstruction.text: If IV unavailable, and if unable to drink by mouth, give      1840ml  over 6 hours

medicationCodeableConcept.text: Lactated Ringers or Normal Saline (clinic or hospital)

dosageInstruction.text: If hemoglobin > 5, give     Lactated Ringers or Normal Saline (clinic or hospital) 460ml (or cc)  over 1 hour then give     1070ml (or cc)  over 5 hours

medicationCodeableConcept.text: Extra for diarrhea: ORS by mouth

dosageInstruction.text: Start  3 1/2 - 5 1/2   cup(s)    or 840-1320 ml     every 4 hours until urine is clear or there is a normal number of wet diapers
Consider Starting   190mg   Cefalexin   or  380-760mg  IM Cloxacillin 4 times a day for 5 days
Start    tablet(s)  (250mg) 2 times a day for 3 days
Start   770mg   Ceftriaxone 2 times a day  or  770mg   Cefotaxime 3 times a day or every 8 hours for 10 days
Start   2mg IM  Dexamethasone 4 times a day for 4 days . Give same time as antibiotics

Start Cotrimoxazole. Give  3   tablet(s) (20mg Trimethroprim + 100mg Sulfamethoxazole / 5ml)   or 2 1/2  teaspoon syrup (40mg Trimethroprim + 200mg Sulfamethoxazole / 5ml) 2 times a day for 5 days . If Cotrimoxazole not available use treatment for Amoxicillin
Start  1/2  teaspoon syrup Ferrous Fumarate (100mg/5ml)  once per day for 14 days or 1/2   tablet(s) Ferrous Sulfate-Folate (250mg / 250ug) 1 times a day for 14 days
Start  3  dispersible tablet(s) Amoxicillin (250mg)   or 15 ml (250mg / 5ml syrup)    twice per day for 10 days
Apply tetracycline eye ointment both eyes four times per day until drainage stops
